Map Description:

This is a de map, but it, like my other de maps, is weighted towards the CTs instead of the Ts for a change.  This map is based underwater, and contains 2 main levels.  You spawn at the highest level (Ts on 1 side, CTs on the other, separated by an unbreakable metal wall).  The bombsite is located underwater, past to blast doors, and the bombsite area is radioactive, so plant fast (and no camping).  Since prolonged exposure underwater will cause you to drown, there are several openings (surrounded by ubreakable glass) to allow you to breathe.  Miss one, and you will not make it to the next without losing a substantial amount of health.  if you manage to get to air after you lose health, stay above water for long enough, and you will regain it.  However, if you are spotted  by a camper through the glass, you can be shot.  The damage is less since the bullet is flying through glass, but be careful.  After swimming from air pocket to air pocket for about 200 yards, you come to a blast door that opens painfully slowly.  After that, there is a simillar 200 yard jaunt before you reach another painfully slow blast door, past this is the radioactive bombsite (you lose 1 health per every half second in that room.  Running that route with no interference takes about 45 seconds.  Also, this map requires flashlights, since during that underwater route the only light (apart from a radioactive hazard red strobe) comes from the glass enclosed air pockets.  Therefore, CTs can camp or rush, but camping is limited.  And Ts, get off your ass, that route takes forever.  have fun, and check out my other maps!

DE ATLANTIS =========== by FireWavezZ & Gmaps --------------------- Since the discovery of a mysterious object on the ocean floor by a sweedish salvage ship, government and military forces controlling the site have made no official statements as to what is there. We can only speculate as to what has been found (there has been talk of alien spacecraft and lost cities) but it is obviously something of great importance. However, curiosity is now turning to concern. Whilst still no official statement has been forthcoming, reporters and observers have noted a dramatic change in activity aournd the site in recent days. All "scientific" traffic has been stopped and large numbers of people have been moved out of the "quarenteen zone" (10 miles around the site) The only people who have been seen going towards the site are military and special forces operatives. * Counter-Terrorists: Save Atlantis... * Terrorists: Destroy this underwater paradise > Special credit room underneath the map. The layout idea of the map is that the facility is an old worn down naval base. The submarine (custom model by Frenzy) is based on the UK nuclear submarine Astute. The submarine is bombsite A (as in astute) and in the underground trainyard bombsite B is located. We have tried to make the map from a tactical point of view and from beta testing found it quite a challenge for both teams, once you know the map well enough.  There are 20 spawn points available for each team. We have found that the map easily holds 10 players on each team. We have tried to play around with light and sound to create a fitting mood for the map.

The major change from the Beta version of the map is a new route to the side of the ramp leading to Astute with access from the lower level via a security door.  This was done to help encourage the T's to attack Astute.  The train yard was also modified to make it easier to defend.  A number of changes have also been made to help frame rates in the sub room.

Overview and Nav file is included in the BSP as well as all custom props, decals, textures etc.

The layout idea of the map is that the facility is an old worn down naval base. The submarine (custom model by Frenzy) is based on the UK nuclear submarine Astute. The submarine is bombsite A (as in astute) and in the underground trainyard bombsite B is located. We have tried to make the map from a tactical point of view and from beta testing found it quite a challenge for both teams, once you know the map well enough. In previous versions we have had more routes but it became too unbalanced in T favour and the current layout seems to be the most even. There are 20 spawn points available for each team. We have found that the map easily holds 10 players on each team. We have tried to play around with light and sound to create a fitting mood for the map.

WHERE DID THE IDEA COME FROM?

The Area 65 map came to me when i was playing Project I.G.I, it is a map which the main character has to infiltrate. So i thought that this would make a really cool CS:S map. So i took some screenshots did some planning and i have begun work on it.

WHAT IS IT ABOUT?

Out in an unknown desert, the military facility Area 65 is a top devision which works on counter-terrorist tactics and communications. After recently finding information about a powerful terrorist group, the base lost communications with its check point.

Counter Terrorists:
Your mission is to prevent Terrorists from arming and destructing a bomb with Area 65. If a bomb were to go off, all information regarding counter-terrorist activities would be lost and our battle against Terrorism would be lost. You must ensure that the base remains in tact and that all enemy units are defeated. All non-combatant personel have been removed from the base, the only people who you should watch your fire on are your own team mates. Everyone else is to be eleminiated sight.

Terrorists:
My Friends, today we move against the enemy in an offensive which could bring their counter-terrorist forces to their knees. We must plant a bomb at either Bomb Site A or B, this bomb on detonation will destroy all information on our where about and tactics. Rendering them useless. My friends, fight for Victory.

PROBLEMS/BUGS:

De_area52, originally from my favorite console shooter, Perfect Dark, was one of my first maps. I started it not knowing much about map making, for almost 2 years I worked on and off with it. Again, every time I would learn something new I would implement it into the map. After 2 totally different versions of the map I decided to go through it once more, use my abilities to optimize it and make it worth the wait.

People were always telling me to "make use of the Source engine" those words stuck with me for a long time. I kept having trouble debating on if I was “sourcifing” the map too much or not enough. At it’s final state I think I hit a good blend between the two. Though I still think there are areas that are too plain, I’m proud and happy with the final result.
